f our cases the\nphase shifts can be explained by differential rotation: Two spot regions move\nwith different angular velocity and even pass each other. Comparison between\nthe methods show that the carrier fit utility is better in retrieving slow\nevolution especially from a low amplitude light curve, while the continuous\nperiod search is more sensitive in case of rapid changes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Nov 2012 16:30:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 22 Mar 2013 14:12:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
