cts preserve Lorentz symmetry, but their variance is non-zero.\nInterestingly, the particle/antiparticle asymmetry comes out naturally to\nfavour matter over antimatter in this third background, once the effects of the\nkinematics of the scattering of the D branes with matter is incorporated.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Nov 2012 18:44:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
